<!--
    ===========================================================================
    WHAT OUTSIDE CONTROLS ARE
    ===========================================================================
    Two separate outside-cab controls can be added to a TANKER via its
    fillPoints.xml (see TANKER SETUP below):

      ptoControl        Turns the PTO / pump ON and OFF from a node on the
                        tanker. The cab PTO control ALWAYS stays as well — this
                        is an ADDITIONAL place to do it. It only appears in-game
                        if the attached TRACTOR is allowed outside PTO (decided
                        by this file or by the tractor's own marker, below).

      directionControl  RELOCATES the fill/empty flow-direction control out of
                        the cab to a node on the tanker. Nothing to do with
                        valves. If this node is present, direction can ONLY be
                        set at the node and is removed from the cab. If it is
                        NOT present, direction stays in the cab as normal. Used
                        for vac tankers that cannot switch direction from the
                        cab in real life. This does NOT depend on the tractor.

    ===========================================================================
    THE TWO TIERS (how the script decides if a tractor allows outside PTO)
    ===========================================================================
    Tier 1  The TRACTOR carries its own marker inside its vehicle.xml. Best for
            anyone who OWNS the tractor mod — it is self-contained and needs no
            entry in this file. Tier 1 always overrides Tier 2.

    Tier 2  THIS FILE lists tractors by configFileName path-tail. Use it for
            tractors you do NOT control: base-game tractors, or third-party
            tractors whose author never added a Tier 1 marker.

    Only the PTO control is gated by tractor capability. directionControl is a
    property of the tanker and is never listed here.

    ===========================================================================
    HOW TO GET A REAL PATH (do not guess — read it from the log)
    ===========================================================================
    1. Load the tractor in-game and enter it.
    2. Open the console and run:  spsCap
    3. It prints "resolved tractor: <full path>".
    4. Copy the TAIL of that path (starting at data/... for base game, or at
       FS25_.../... for a mod) into a <vehicle path="..."> row below.

    Path-tail rule (identical to spsConfigManifest.xml): a row matches when the
    tractor's full configFileName ENDS with #path, case-insensitive, forward
    slashes only.
      Base-game tail example:  data/vehicles/brandX/modelY/modelY.xml
      Mod tail example:        FS25_BrandX_ModelY/modelY.xml

    Capability flags (all default to false if omitted):
      pto         outside PTO / pump on-off allowed
      hydraulics  reserved for a future outside-hydraulics control
      lift        reserved for a future outside-lift control
-->

