<!-- ========================================================================= -->
<!-- TIER 1 — MODDER'S OWN TRACTOR  (goes in the TRACTOR'S vehicle.xml)        -->
<!-- ========================================================================= -->
<!--
    If you own the tractor mod, do NOT add it to the list above. Instead add
    ONE line to your tractor's own vehicle.xml as a DIRECT CHILD of <vehicle>.
    Do NOT place it under <slurryPipeSystem> — that path makes SPS treat the
    tractor as a slurry tanker.

        <vehicle>
            ...
            <spsOutsideControls pto="true" hydraulics="false" lift="false"/>
            ...
        </vehicle>

    Only "pto" matters today; the others are reserved. Omitted flags = false.
-->

<!-- ========================================================================= -->
<!-- TANKER SETUP  (goes in the TANKER'S SPS fillPoints.xml)                   -->
<!-- ========================================================================= -->
<!--
    Outside controls are declared on the TANKER, inside <slurryPipeSystem>.
    Each control points at a node defined in the tanker's nodeTree.i3d. Add
    only the controls that tanker should have.

    <slurryPipeSystem>
        ...

        Outside PTO on/off node (cab PTO also stays). Appears in-game only when
        the attached tractor is PTO-capable per Tier 1 or Tier 2 above:

        <ptoControls>
            <ptoControl mountNodeName="ptoControl01"/>
        </ptoControls>

        Outside flow-direction node. Presence MOVES fill/empty direction out of
        the cab to this node. Omit the whole block to keep direction in the cab:

        <directionControls>
            <directionControl mountNodeName="pumpControl01"/>
        </directionControls>

        ...
    </slurryPipeSystem>

    NOTE on the TSA-style trailer: it keeps using the existing
        <pumpControls><pumpControl nodeName="rearControlNode" radius="1.5"/></pumpControls>
    block, which is the all-in-one node for cabless trailers. That block is
    unchanged and is NOT the same as the two blocks above. Do not mix them on
    the same tanker.
-->